{{see also|List of IFK Göteborg players|Category:IFK Göteborg players}}
Sixteen of the following players have either been chosen for the greatest ever IFK Göteborg team in a 2004 poll by readers of the regional newspaper [[Göteborgs-Posten]],<ref name="greatest11a">Jönsson, p. 356.</ref> or have been chosen for the dream team presented in the club's official 100 year jubilee book published in 2004.<ref name="greatest11b">Jönsson, p. 8.</ref> (Some are present in both lineups.) Another two players who have gained more than 90 caps for the national team are also included. The players are listed according to when they debuted for IFK Göteborg (year in parentheses):
*1900s&ndash;1920s: [[Erik Börjesson]] (1907), [[Filip Johansson|Filip 'Svarte-Filip' Johansson]] (1924)
*1930s&ndash;1940s: [[Arne Nyberg]] (1932), [[Gunnar Gren]] (1940)
*1950s&ndash;1960s: [[Bengt Berndtsson|Bengt 'Fölet' Berndtsson]] (1950), [[Bertil Johansson|Bertil 'Bebben' Johansson]] (1954), [[Donald Niklasson]] (1967)
*1970s: [[Torbjörn Nilsson]] (1975), [[Tommy Holmgren]] (1977), [[Glenn Hysén]] (1978), [[Ruben Svensson]] (1978), [[Glenn Strömberg]] (1979)
*1980s: [[Stig Fredriksson]] (1980), [[Roland Nilsson]] (1983), [[Håkan Mild]] (1988), [[Thomas Ravelli]] (1989)
*1990s: [[Magnus Erlingmark]] (1993), [[Niclas Alexandersson]] (1996)

== Noted managers ==
''Listed according to when they became managers for IFK Göteborg (year in parentheses):''
*1910s&ndash;1940s: [[Jozef Nagy]] (1945)
*1950s&ndash;1980s: [[Bertil Johansson|Bertil 'Bebben' Johansson]] (1967), [[Sven-Göran Eriksson]] (1979)
*1990s&ndash;2000s: [[Roger Gustafsson]] (1990), [[Bo Johansson|Bosse Johansson]] (2003)

== Achievements ==
{{main|IFK Göteborg records}}

=== Domestic ===
*'''[[Swedish football champions|Swedish Champions]]:'''
**'''Winners (18):''' 1908, 1910, 1918, 1934&ndash;35, 1941&ndash;42, 1957&ndash;58, 1969, 1982, 1983, 1984, 1987, 1990, 1991, 1993, 1994, 1995, 1996, 2007
*'''[[Allsvenskan]]:'''
**'''Winners (13):''' 1934&ndash;35, 1941&ndash;42, 1957&ndash;58, 1969, 1982, 1984, 1990, 1991, 1993, 1994, 1995, 1996, 2007
**'''Runners-up (10):''' 1924&ndash;25, 1926&ndash;27, 1929&ndash;30, 1939&ndash;49, 1979, 1981, 1986, 1988, 1997, 2005
*'''[[Mästerskapsserien]]:'''
**'''Winners (1):''' 1991
*'''[[Allsvenskan]] play-off:'''
**'''Winners (5):''' 1982, 1983, 1984, 1987, 1990
**'''Runners-up (1):''' 1985
*'''[[Svenska Serien]]:'''
**'''Winners (5):''' 1912&ndash;13, 1913&ndash;14, 1914&ndash;15, 1915&ndash;16, 1916&ndash;17
*'''[[Fyrkantserien]]:'''
**'''Winners (1):''' 1918, 1919
*'''[[Svenska Mästerskapet]]:'''
**'''Winners (3):''' 1908, 1910, 1918
*'''[[Svenska Cupen]]:'''
**'''Winners (5):''' 1978&ndash;79, 1981&ndash;82, 1982&ndash;83, 1991, 2008
**'''Runners-up (4):''' 1985&ndash;86, 1998&ndash;99, 2004, 2007
*'''[[Supercupen]]:'''
**'''Winners (1):''' 2008

=== European ===
*'''[[UEFA Cup]]:'''
**'''Winners (2):''' 1981&ndash;82, 1986&ndash;87
*'''[[Royal League]]:'''
**'''Runners-up (1):''' 2004&ndash;05

== Records ==
{{main|IFK Göteborg records}}
*Home victory, Allsvenskan: 9&ndash;1 vs. [[IK Sleipner]], [[10 May]] [[1925]]; 8&ndash;0 vs. [[Hammarby IF]], [[2 June]] [[1925]]; 8&ndash;0 vs. [[Stattena IF]], [[21 April]] [[1930]]
*Away victory, Allsvenskan: 9&ndash;2 vs. [[IFK Eskilstuna]], [[8 October]] [[1933]]; 7&ndash;0 vs. [[IK Sleipner]], [[20 April]] [[1941]]
*Home loss, Allsvenskan: 2&ndash;9 vs. [[Malmö FF]], [[10 September]] [[1949]]
*Away loss, Allsvenskan: 0&ndash;7 vs. [[IFK Norrköping]], [[1 May]] [[1960]]
*Highest attendance, [[Ullevi|Nya Ullevi]]: 52,194 vs. [[Örgryte IS]], [[3 June]] [[1959]]
*Highest attendance, [[Gamla Ullevi]]: 31,064 vs. [[GAIS]], [[27 May]] [[1955]]
*Highest attendance, [[Slottsskogsvallen]]: 21,580 vs. [[AIK Fotboll|AIK]], [[25 October]] [[1931]]
*Highest average attendance, season: 23,796, 1977
*Most appearances, total: 609, [[Mikael Nilsson (born 1968)|Mikael Nilsson]] 1987&ndash;2001
*Most appearances, Allsvenskan: 348, [[Bengt Berndtsson]] 1951&ndash;1967
*Most goals scored, total: 333, [[Filip Johansson]] 1924&ndash;1934
*Most goals scored, Allsvenskan: 180, [[Filip Johansson]] 1924&ndash;1934
*Most goals scored, season, Allsvenskan: 39, [[Filip Johansson]] 1924&ndash;25

